  "canonical_explanation": {
    "text": "Plants are living things that make their own food using sunlight, water, and air. Different parts of plants have different jobs: roots absorb water, stems carry water and support the plant, leaves make food through photosynthesis, and flowers help in reproduction. Plants adapt to their environment - desert plants store water, water plants float.",
